+</span><span id="TransitionResolver-24"><a href="#TransitionResolver-24"><span class="linenos"> 24</span></a><span class="sd">    Evaluates a node&#39;s transition list against live NPC state to determine</span>
+</span><span id="TransitionResolver-25"><a href="#TransitionResolver-25"><span class="linenos"> 25</span></a><span class="sd">    which node to route to next.</span>
+</span><span id="TransitionResolver-26"><a href="#TransitionResolver-26"><span class="linenos"> 26</span></a>
+</span><span id="TransitionResolver-27"><a href="#TransitionResolver-27"><span class="linenos"> 27</span></a><span class="sd">    Transitions are evaluated in order — first match wins.</span>
+</span><span id="TransitionResolver-28"><a href="#TransitionResolver-28"><span class="linenos"> 28</span></a><span class="sd">    This is where the scenario becomes truly NPC-agnostic: same choices,</span>
+</span><span id="TransitionResolver-29"><a href="#TransitionResolver-29"><span class="linenos"> 29</span></a><span class="sd">    different NPC states, different paths.</span>
+</span><span id="TransitionResolver-30"><a href="#TransitionResolver-30"><span class="linenos"> 30</span></a>
+</span><span id="TransitionResolver-31"><a href="#TransitionResolver-31"><span class="linenos"> 31</span></a><span class="sd">    The resolver supports simple expression evaluation for transition conditions,</span>
+</span><span id="TransitionResolver-32"><a href="#TransitionResolver-32"><span class="linenos"> 32</span></a><span class="sd">    including:</span>
+</span><span id="TransitionResolver-33"><a href="#TransitionResolver-33"><span class="linenos"> 33</span></a><span class="sd">    - player_relation: The NPC&#39;s relationship with the player</span>
+</span><span id="TransitionResolver-34"><a href="#TransitionResolver-34"><span class="linenos"> 34</span></a><span class="sd">    - turn_count: Number of conversation turns so far</span>
+</span><span id="TransitionResolver-35"><a href="#TransitionResolver-35"><span class="linenos"> 35</span></a><span class="sd">    - Basic comparison operators: ==, !=, &lt;, &gt;, &lt;=, &gt;=, and, or</span>
+</span><span id="TransitionResolver-36"><a href="#TransitionResolver-36"><span class="linenos"> 36</span></a>
+</span><span id="TransitionResolver-37"><a href="#TransitionResolver-37"><span class="linenos"> 37</span></a><span class="sd">    Example transition conditions:</span>
+</span><span id="TransitionResolver-38"><a href="#TransitionResolver-38"><span class="linenos"> 38</span></a><span class="sd">    - &quot;player_relation &gt; 0.5&quot;</span>
+</span><span id="TransitionResolver-39"><a href="#TransitionResolver-39"><span class="linenos"> 39</span></a><span class="sd">    - &quot;turn_count &gt;= 3&quot;</span>
+</span><span id="TransitionResolver-40"><a href="#TransitionResolver-40"><span class="linenos"> 40</span></a><span class="sd">    - &quot;player_relation &lt; 0 and turn_count &gt; 1&quot;</span>
+</span><span id="TransitionResolver-41"><a href="#TransitionResolver-41"><span class="linenos"> 41</span></a><span class="sd">    &quot;&quot;&quot;</span>
+</span><span id="TransitionResolver-42"><a href="#TransitionResolver-42"><span class="linenos"> 42</span></a>
+</span><span id="TransitionResolver-43"><a href="#TransitionResolver-43"><span class="linenos"> 43</span></a>    <span class="c1"># Simple expression evaluator for transition conditions.</span>
+</span><span id="TransitionResolver-44"><a href="#TransitionResolver-44"><span class="linenos"> 44</span></a>    <span class="c1"># Supports: player_relation, turn_count, and basic comparisons.</span>
